- "sea of cinematic achievement" refers to the extensive collection of movies and their accolades; 
- "leading stars" denotes actors who are the lead actors in movies;
- "ships have sailed towards the shores of nomination" is a metaphor for movies that have received nominations.

sql:
SELECT title 
FROM movies 
WHERE total_gross = (SELECT MAX(total_gross) FROM movies);

SELECT SUM(total_gross) AS total_revenue
FROM movies
WHERE studio_id = (SELECT studio_id FROM studios WHERE studio_name = '<specific_studio_name>');

SELECT title, year 
FROM movies 
WHERE studio_id = 123 AND sequel = 1;
